QSTRUP gives in Mar. D. Ost-Gronl. Tab. 4, f. 30 a figure of a small form, that Ι believe identical with the present one. Mr QSTRUP refers it, with hesitation, to Navicula bahusz'ensis GRUN., but 1 cannot join him in this determination, as the latter is a broad, obtuse species, I believe in contrary-Na- vicula ammophila to be the nearest relation, as this species has acute ends and a similar striation.
